data.text/html:
**y = 0.0 + 1.0×x + 2.0×Group + 0.5×(x×Group)** (where Group = 0 for Control, 1 for Treatment)

Shows the relationship between predictor and outcome. Look for: linear pattern, spread of points around line.
Checks model assumptions. Look for: random scatter around zero (good), patterns/funnel shapes (bad — suggests non-linearity or heteroscedasticity).

Coefficient Interpretation (Multivariable, RAOS Style)

Intercept (β₀ = 0.0): For Control (when Group=0), when x=0, the predicted y is 0.0. Slope of x (β₁ = 1.0): Comparing two observations with the same Group, a 1-unit difference in x corresponds to a 1.0-unit higher y. Group Effect (β₂ = 2.0): Comparing Treatment to Control at the same x, Treatment has 2.0 units higher y when x=0. Interaction (β₃ = 0.5): The effect of x on y is 0.5 units stronger for Treatment than for Control. (Slope for Control: 1.0, Slope for Treatment: 1.5)
